Person Record Management System
This Java Swing application allows users to manage Person records. Users can add new Person records, save them to a file, and load records from a file.

Features
Add Person:
Input a person's name and age.'
Add the person to an internal list.
Display the number of records in the list.

Save Records:
Save all person records to a file in a specified format.

Load Records:
Load person records from a file and display them.

Key Components
Person Class
Attributes:
name: The person's name.
age: The person's age.

Methods:
getName(), setName(), getAge(), setAge(): Getters and setters for attributes.
toString(): Returns a string representation of the person in the format "name
".

GUI Actions
Add Person (btnaddActionPerformed):
Reads the name and age from text fields.
Creates a new Person object and adds it to the persons list.
Clears the text fields and updates the display with the count of records.
Save Records (btnsaveActionPerformed):

Converts each Person object to a string.
Writes the records to a file.
Handles potential IOException during file operations.
Load Records (btnloadActionPerformed):

Clears the existing list of Person objects.
Reads records from a file and reconstructs Person objects.
Displays the loaded records.
Handles potential FileNotFoundException and IOException during file operations.
Files
File Path:

Default path is set to C:\\Users\\Hp\\Desktop.
File Name:

The file where records are saved or loaded from is named sano.dat.
